description.narrative: 9.77 million children from pre-primary to grade-5 (6-10 years) were reached with remote learning, 4,300 children benefited from the accelerated education programme, and 180,000 children of 657 schools in Cox’s Bazar district reached through direct interventions. An integrated EMIS for the primary education subsector was developed, and a pilot on School and Classroom-Based Assessment in 100 primary schools was completed. The disaster risk reduction/education in the emergency framework was approved and is being operationalized through guidelines. The approval of the National Curriculum Framework created momentum for qualitative changes in teaching-learning processes and is contributing to improving learning outcomes for children. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:22/12/2021
